# Docker stack rules

- **Source of truth:** [`docker/CONVENTIONS.md`](docker/CONVENTIONS.md) — infrastructure must use **published OCI images** (Mongo, MinIO, Mailpit, Nginx, Node base); default compose must not require **Vercel Blob**, **SendGrid**, **Cloudflare R2**, or **Algolia** for core CMS + uploads + mail capture.
- **Payload:** DB [`src/lib/payloadDb.ts`](src/lib/payloadDb.ts); storage [`src/plugins/storage/config.ts`](src/plugins/storage/config.ts) (`S3_*` → MinIO); email [`src/payload.config.ts`](src/payload.config.ts) (`SMTP_*` → Mailpit).
- **Docs:** [DOCKER.md](DOCKER.md) for operator steps; optional SaaS (Stripe, GitHub fetch, Algolia) stays optional per CONVENTIONS.

When adding services: prefer **official** or **widely used** images on Docker Hub / quay.io; document the SaaS equivalent they replace in `docker/CONVENTIONS.md`.

**Doc search:** `src/app/(frontend)/api/docs-local-search/route.ts` uses **`rg`** only when **not** `deploymentTarget === 'cloudflare'` and env is set — keeps Cloudflare Workers + Vercel builds safe.
